author_ssm: Valerie S. Komor and Bobby Lee (2003); migrated to ArchivesSpace by Joseph Ditta (2020).
abstract_ssm: Drypoints by Polish-born artist Mortimer Borne (1902–1987) depicting Manhattan streets, skylines, harbors, churches, parks (especially Central Park), and elevated trains. Includes views of Brooklyn, Sheepshead Bay, Coney Island, Spuyten Duyvil, and the 1939–1940 World's Fair Grounds at night.
